1. Search for Azure Database for MySQL flexible servers --> create --> Flexible server = advance create --> choose central us --> networking = for public acces no vnet required and for private
   vnet is required, click on Allow public access from any Azure service within Azure to this server, click Add current client IP  --> review and create.

2. After create copy the endpoint and you can connet through mysql workbench or with connect option --> create any database --> Go to settings and check all the options

3. Go to Replication --> Add replica --> give name and create it --> connect the reader --> check all the databases.

4. Go to compute and service --> you can increase Backup retention period to 35 days and save  --> Go to Backup and restore --> select on demand and create backup

5. Search for Storage Account --> give any unique name --> sotrage type = Azure blob, workload = other, and create it.

6. After successfully storage account creates --> Data Storage --> create containers --> upload file --> click on file and take url and access it. --> If public access not permitted

7. Go to storage account --> setting --> configurations --> Allow Blob anonymous access = enable --> save

8. Go to containers --> select container --> change access level --> Blob --> then check url you will able to access.

9. Go to Data management --> static website --> enable --> index.html --> save it --> go to containers --> web container will be create select that and upload index.html file 

10. Go to static website --> copy primary endpoint and access the website.

11. Go to your created container and delete file --> select show active and deleted blobs --> undelete file 

12. Go to Data protection --> enable versioning for blobs --> save --> then you can check the version of file and restore any version 



